1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
India's real risk is not one oil spike. It is too many chokepoints at once.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,000
If Hormuz, the Red Sea, or Suez tighten, fuel, data, and cargo all feel it.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:12,000
The fix is not panic. It is redundancy.

4
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:17,000
Buy oil from more places, from Russia and the Gulf to the U.S., Brazil, and West Africa.

5
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Fill bigger strategic reserves so India can absorb shocks instead of reacting to them.

6
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Build more cable landings and reroute traffic east and west when one line breaks.

7
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Move cargo through Chabahar, Vladivostok, Sittwe, Bangladesh routes, and stronger Indian ports.

8
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Real security is not one route. It is backup after backup after backup.

9
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,200
Oil, data, or cargo: which backup matters most next?
